  "2026-07-14T22:56:36.829Z",codex-root,"Implementation start 2026-07-15: bundled with pm-3mna because global author attribution, init author_default, config persistence, and health/validate remediation share the same workspace-customization primitives. Live GH-444 and all-status duplicate lineage confirmed this is canonical."
  "2026-07-14T23:44:01.801Z",unknown,"Verification evidence 2026-07-15: final all-source coverage passed 291 files / 5,708 tests at exact 100% (36,925 statements, 26,508 branches, 7,449 functions, 36,040 lines). Packed clean-install proof confirms global --author precedence for init/create/comments, non-empty init author_default, exported SDK program/scanner primitives, and advisory non-blocking unknown-author health/validate diagnostics. Release readiness passed all code/package/security gates and stops only on separately tracked external Sentry highs; live telemetry is healthy at 0.34% errors with complete error codes."
  "2026-07-15T00:04:34.200Z",unknown,"Greptile pre-push review 6357789e-57bf-4116-be0e-52d29e120d5b: accepted both findings. Bootstrap author parsing now preserves following flags under Commander optional-value semantics, and invocation-author validation runs inside the central CLI catch/finally path so formatted errors, telemetry, exit codes, and environment restoration remain intact. Regression suite passes 132/132; final all-source coverage passes 291 files / 5,709 tests at exact 100%: 36,933 statements, 26,518 branches, 7,451 functions, 36,048 lines. Strict lint/static/package-boundary/token gates remain green."
  "2026-07-15T00:04:44.823Z",codex-root,"Attribution correction: the immediately preceding two verification comments were written by codex-root from shell calls that omitted PM_AUTHOR against this legacy tracker, and are intentionally preserved append-only as live evidence for the new advisory. All subsequent mutations set explicit attribution; no history is rewritten."
  "2026-07-15T00:14:44.637Z",codex-root,"Greptile pre-push rerun 5b5f653b-6605-467e-84a2-176f40445f0a completed at confidence 5/5, safe to merge, with no review comments. It explicitly verified both prior blockers resolved: flag-like tokens are not consumed as optional author values, and author override validation/restoration stays within the central catch/finally lifecycle."
  "2026-07-15T01:07:24.805Z",codex-root,"PR #565 round-1 and packed acceptance evidence: global --author now requires an explicit non-flag value, missing values flow through the central JSON/telemetry error path, empty rendered commands are stable, fresh init persists a non-empty default, legacy blank-setting fallback remains explicitly covered, and scoped validate avoids unrelated attribution scans. Final all-source coverage is exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,713 tests. A fresh installed tarball proved init/create/comments author precedence plus zero unknown history events through the public SDK scanner."
  "2026-07-15T01:47:04.851Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile consistency follow-up: although the review was confidence 5/5 with no comments, its reasoning noted that inline-empty --author= lacked the structured code/next_steps supplied for a missing value. Both malformed forms now emit missing_required_argument plus the explicit --author <id> recovery step through the central JSON handler. Focused tests pass 132/132 and final all-source coverage remains exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,713 tests."
