body: "GitHub: https://github.com/unbraind/pm-cli/issues/444\n\n## Problem\nMutations fall back to author \"unknown\" when PM_AUTHOR is unset and author_default is empty (the init default). Stateless CLI agents get a fresh env per shell call, so attribution silently degrades to \"unknown\" — breaking history/claims/comments provenance that multi-agent coordination depends on.\n\n## Proposed fix\n(1) top-level global `--author <id>` flag; (2) `pm init` records a stable author_default (prompt or derive from git config/hostname); (3) pm health/validate warning when recent mutations carry author \"unknown\" with fix-hint `pm config set author-default <id>`.\n\n## Definition of done\nGlobal --author works on all mutations; init writes a non-empty author_default; unknown-author advisory ships with remediation-registry entry; docs/AGENTS.md updated. Related: GH-458 item covers the claim-time --assignee alias."
